title: Strong Growth in Final Consumption Expenditure
description: In 2022, Tajikistan experienced a significant growth in final consumption expenditure, with an annual increase of 14.33%. This indicates a robust domestic demand and economic activity.

title: Full Binding Coverage on All Products
description: Tajikistan achieved a 100% binding coverage on all products in 2021, ensuring comprehensive trade commitments and tariff bindings.

title: Full Binding Coverage on Primary Products
description: In 2021, Tajikistan also secured a 100% binding coverage on primary products, reflecting strong trade policy measures.

title: Low Unemployment Among Highly Educated
description: As of 2016, only 0.24% of the labor force with advanced education in Tajikistan was unemployed, indicating effective utilization of skilled labor.

title: Minimal Early Marriages Among Women
description: In 2017, only 0.1% of women aged 20-24 in Tajikistan were married by age 15, reflecting progress in women's rights and education.

title: Limited Domestic Credit Availability
description: In 2023, domestic credit provided by the financial sector in Tajikistan was only 11.31% of GDP, indicating limited financial sector development.

title: Low Investment in Transport Infrastructure
description: In 2022, Tajikistan saw an investment of only $4.5 million in transport with private participation, highlighting a need for increased infrastructure funding.

title: Limited Public-Private Partnerships in Transport
description: The investment in public-private partnerships for transport in 2022 was also $4.5 million, suggesting a need for more collaborative infrastructure projects.
